    <segment id="1" parent="14" relname="concession">
Although all the features/attributes mentioned above are important in the design of an application,</segment>
    <segment id="14" parent="40" relname="span"> some of the features/attributes that stand out, in my experience are: -- ease of use, -- ease of learning and -- error recovery.</segment>
    <segment id="2" parent="36" relname="preparation"> 
Ease of Use:</segment>
    <segment id="18" parent="15" relname="condition"> If an application is not easy to use,</segment>
    <segment id="15" parent="24" relname="span"> none of the users are going to be very happy using it.</segment>
    <segment id="3" parent="25" relname="span"> If the users are not happy, then the productivity goes down.</segment>
    <segment id="4" parent="26" relname="span"> Every application must be made in a way it is easy to be used,</segment>
    <segment id="19" parent="4" relname="antithesis"> no matter if it is of superior quality.</segment>
    <segment id="5" parent="29" relname="span"> The best example would be Windows Vs Unix.</segment>
    <segment id="6" parent="17" relname="concession"> Although Unix is a far superior OS,</segment>
    <segment id="17" parent="27" relname="span"> Windows is the choice of 95% of the worlds computer users.</segment>
    <segment id="7" parent="28" relname="span"> And one of the most important reason for this is, ease of use.</segment>
    <segment id="8" parent="34" relname="preparation"> 
Ease of learning:</segment>
    <segment id="16" parent="34" relname="span"> Ease of use should and will be complimented with the ease of learning.</segment>
    <segment id="9" parent="20" relname="condition"> If users cannot learn to use the application easily,</segment>
    <segment id="20" parent="32" relname="span"> then they will not be too happy implementing the product.</segment>
    <segment id="10" parent="31" relname="span"> Not only are the users unhappy with the applications implementation,</segment>
    <segment id="21" parent="10" relname="elaboration"> the management will also be unhappy becasue they will have to spend more time and money training the users.</segment>
    <segment id="11" parent="35" relname="preparation"> 
Error recovery: </segment>
    <segment id="22" parent="23" relname="condition">No matter how good the application is, if it does not have proper error recovery mechanism,</segment>
    <segment id="23" parent="35" relname="span"> it will not be very popular with the majority of users.</segment>
    <segment id="12" parent="13" relname="preparation"> This is especially true when business are taken into consideration.</segment>
    <segment id="13" parent="33" relname="span"> Data is money and businesses cannot afford to lose data.</segment>
